---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="Scrabble Words Ending in Z — Top Scoring Plays (2026)" description="Master words ending in Z for Scrabble. JAZZ (29pts), FIZZ (25pts), BUZZ (24pts), QUIZ (22pts), WALTZ (17pts), BLITZ (16pts). Z-ending strategy guide inside." keywords="scrabble words ending in z, words ending in z scrabble, z ending words, jazz scrabble, fizz scrabble, buzz scrabble, quiz scrabble, waltz scrabble, blitz scrabble">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words Ending in Z — Top Scoring Plays","description":"Master words ending in Z for Scrabble. JAZZ (29pts), FIZZ (25pts), BUZZ (24pts), QUIZ (22pts), WALTZ (17pts), BLITZ (16pts) and more.","datePublished":"2026-06-29","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-z"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the highest-scoring Scrabble words ending in Z?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The top Z-ending words are JAZZ (29pts), FIZZ (25pts), BUZZ (24pts), QUIZ (22pts), WALTZ (17pts), BLITZ (16pts), FRIZZ (26pts), and PIZZAZZ (45pts). Double-Z words dominate because Z is worth 10 points each."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why are words ending in Z so powerful in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Z is worth 10 points — the joint highest tile value alongside Q. Words ending in Z can't be easily extended by opponents since very few letters hook after Z. Many Z-ending words also contain double-Z (JAZZ, FIZZ, BUZZ), scoring 20 points from Z tiles alone."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you pluralize words ending in Z in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Some Z-ending words can add -ES (BUZZES, FIZZES, QUIZZES) but not a simple S. However, short plays like JAZZ and FIZZ are defensively strong because extending them requires specific tiles. The inability to simply add S makes Z-enders board-locking plays."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words Ending in Z — Top Scoring Plays</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Words ending in Z are the highest-scoring category in Scrabble. Z is worth 10 points per tile, and many Z-ending words stack two Z tiles for devastating scores. JAZZ alone scores 29 points without any premium squares. Here's your complete guide to Z-ending dominance.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Z tile value</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">29</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">JAZZ top score</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1 Z-tile</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">In the bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">No S-hook</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Defensive</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Elite Tier — 20+ Points</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 LEGENDARY</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">JAZZ</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">29 points · J(8)+A(1)+Z(10)+Z(10) · A genre of music</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The king of Z-ending words. Uses a blank for the second Z in practice (only 1 Z tile exists), but scores 29 in theory. With a blank as one Z, still scores 19. Devastating on any premium square.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">FIZZ — 25 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">F(4)+I(1)+Z(10)+Z(10). To bubble or effervesce. Needs a blank for second Z.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">BUZZ — 24 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">B(3)+U(1)+Z(10)+Z(10). A humming sound. Another double-Z powerhouse.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">QUIZ — 22 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Q(10)+U(1)+I(1)+Z(10). A test. Uses both Q and Z for maximum value.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">FUZZ — 25 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">F(4)+U(1)+Z(10)+Z(10). Soft fibres. Same score as FIZZ with different vowel.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strong Tier — 15-19 Points</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WALTZ</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">17pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BLITZ</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">16pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">GLITZ</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HERTZ</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">17pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FRITZ</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">17pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">KLUTZ</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">18pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TOPAZ</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">16pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SPITZ</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">16pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Z-Ending Strategy</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Use blanks for double-Z:</span> Only 1 Z tile exists in the bag. To play JAZZ, FIZZ, or BUZZ, you need a blank as the second Z. Save your blank specifically for these monster plays — the point payoff justifies it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Z on TLS = 30 points:</span> A single Z on a Triple Letter Score gives you 30 points from one tile. WALTZ with Z on TLS scores 37 total. Always route Z-ending words toward letter multipliers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Board-locking defense:</span> Z-ending words can't be extended with S. Opponents need very specific tiles to hook. Play Z-enders near board edges for maximum lockdown — protect your lead in endgame.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Pro Tip</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">With only <span class="text-white font-medium">1 Z tile in the standard bag</span>, drawing it gives you an automatic 10+ point advantage. Don't waste Z on low-value plays like ZA (11pts) when you could hold for WALTZ (17pts) or set up JAZZ (29pts) with a blank.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/6-letter-words-with-z/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">6-Letter Words with Z — Top Scoring Scrabble Words</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-z-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Z Words for Scrabble — Complete Scoring Guide</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find all Z-ending words instantly — free solver, no sign-up required</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
